## MODULE 5: 8-HOUR WAR PLAN (300 words max)

> Every minute counts. This plan has ZERO slack time built in — that's intentional. If you finish a phase early, move to UI polish.

| Phase | Time | Duration | Focus |
|-------|------|----------|-------|
| ⚡ SPRINT 1: Setup | 0:00 – 0:30 | 30 min | Repo, Vite scaffold, Flask boilerplate, MongoDB connection, folder structure, design tokens CSS file |
| 🔨 SPRINT 2: Core Build | 0:30 – 3:30 | 3 hr | Backend APIs + DB ∥ Frontend pages + components ∥ AI prompt engineering |
| 🔗 SPRINT 3: Integration | 3:30 – 5:00 | 1.5 hr | Connect frontend ↔ backend ↔ AI, end-to-end golden path works |
| ✨ SPRINT 4: Polish | 5:00 – 6:30 | 1.5 hr | Framer Motion animations, chart animations, responsive fixes, seed demo data, glassmorphism effects |
| 🎤 SPRINT 5: Demo Prep | 6:30 – 8:00 | 1.5 hr | Demo script rehearsal, pitch deck (MAX 5 slides), backup video recording, bug fixes, final git push |

**For each sprint, specify:**

| Sprint | Frontend Dev | Backend Dev | AI Dev | Design/Pitch |
|--------|-------------|-------------|--------|-------------|
| 1 | [exact task] | [exact task] | [exact task] | [exact task] |
| 2 | [exact task] | [exact task] | [exact task] | [exact task] |
| 3 | [exact task] | [exact task] | [exact task] | [exact task] |
| 4 | [exact task] | [exact task] | [exact task] | [exact task] |
| 5 | [exact task] | [exact task] | [exact task] | [exact task] |

**Phase gates (must be TRUE before moving on):**
- After Sprint 1: ✅ App runs locally, API returns test response, DB connected
- After Sprint 2: ✅ All 3 features work independently (even if ugly)
- After Sprint 3: ✅ Golden path works end-to-end (user → input → AI → result displayed)
- After Sprint 4: ✅ App looks premium, animations smooth, demo data loaded
- After Sprint 5: ✅ Pitch rehearsed 2x, backup video exists, team knows click sequence

---

## MODULE 6: PITCH-DEMO FUSION (200 words max)

> In an 8-hour hackathon, you get 3 minutes. Judges are tired. Your PRODUCT must do the talking.

**The 3-Minute Script:**

| Time | Action | Say | Show |
|------|--------|-----|------|
| 0:00–0:15 | HOOK | "[Shocking stat]. [Emotional question]." | Title slide OR product landing page |
| 0:15–0:30 | PROBLEM | "Today, [user] faces [pain]. Existing tools [fail because]." | Nothing — pure eye contact |
| 0:30–0:45 | INTRODUCE | "[Product Name]: [tagline]." | Click into app — hero section visible |
| 0:45–2:00 | LIVE DEMO | Walk through golden path. Narrate every result. | Pre-loaded data, smooth transitions |
| 2:00–2:30 | TECH | "Under the hood: [stack]. AI does [specific thing]." | Architecture slide (1 slide, clean) |
| 2:30–2:45 | IMPACT | "At scale, this reaches [N people] across [context]." | Impact numbers slide |
| 2:45–3:00 | CLOSE | "[Power line — callback to opening hook]." | Product logo + tagline on screen |

**Demo failure protocol:**
1. Golden path pre-loaded with seed data (never type live — all inputs pre-filled)
2. Screen recording backup on phone (if app crashes, play video: "Let me show you what this looks like in action")
3. Test on presentation laptop 30 min before pitch
4. Keep dev server running locally — never depend on deployment/internet

**3 power closing lines (pick best fit):**
- "[Product] doesn't predict the future — it builds it, one [user] at a time."
- "We built this in 8 hours. Imagine what [N users] could do with it in a year."
- "[Problem] has been unsolved for [X years]. [Product] changes that today."

---

## MODULE 7: WINNING PSYCHOLOGY (150 words max)

**What wins 8-hour hackathons (different from 24-48hr events):**

1. **Visual polish wins over feature count.** With 8 hours, a team that builds 2 beautiful features beats a team with 5 ugly ones. Every time.
2. **Pre-built design system = 2 hours saved.** Have your CSS variables, Framer Motion presets, and component shells ready BEFORE the hackathon (if rules allow templates).
3. **Demo data is your secret weapon.** A dashboard with 50 realistic data points looks infinitely more impressive than one with 3 test entries.
4. **The "one thing" rule.** Judges remember ONE feature per team. Make sure yours is unforgettable — either visually stunning or intellectually surprising.
5. **Energy management.** 8 hours = no breaks longer than 10 min. Eat while coding. Designate one person to handle ALL non-coding tasks (pitch, demo data, slides) from hour 5 onward.

**Top 5 fatal mistakes in short hackathons:**
1. Debating the idea past 20 minutes
2. Building auth (zero demo value, 1+ hour cost)
3. Deploying to cloud during hackathon (use localhost)
4. All 4 members coding until minute 0 — nobody prepared the pitch
5. Showing empty/default UI in demo — seed realistic data EARLY

---

## ANTI-PATTERNS (HARD RULES FOR YOUR RESPONSE)

- ❌ Do NOT suggest more than 3 MVP features for an 8-hour hackathon
- ❌ Do NOT provide vague design advice — every visual suggestion must include exact values (hex, px, rem, seconds)
- ❌ Do NOT recommend any feature that takes >90 minutes to build
- ❌ Do NOT suggest deployment during an 8-hour hackathon — localhost only
- ❌ Do NOT write animation descriptions without Framer Motion config objects
- ❌ Do NOT suggest "use Tailwind" — this prompt uses vanilla CSS with design tokens
- ❌ Do NOT give generic pitch advice — provide exact words to say
- ❌ Do NOT suggest more than 4 frontend pages or 6 backend endpoints
```

